edu.rit.crst

Class Concatenate

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.crst.Generator
      • edu.rit.crst.CombiningGenerator
        • edu.rit.crst.Concatenate

  • public class Concatenate
extends CombiningGenerator
    Class Concatenate provides an object that generates input values for a cryptographic Function.

    An instance of class Concatenate is layered on top of two or more other input generators. The latter are specified as arguments to the Concatenate constructor, in the form of constructor expressions. The Concatenate constructor uses the constructor expressions to create the underlying input generators. (For further information about constructor expressions, see class edu.rit.util.Instance.)

    Class Concatenate invokes each underlying input generator to generate a series of cryptographic function input values. Class Concatenate then concatenates these input value series together.
